{"TopicId":178768,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"Need help modding stock airbrakes!","CreatedByName":"everydayastronaut","CreatedById":186030,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-06T14:51:39Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"everydayastronaut","CreatedById":186030,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-06T14:51:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey everyone! Tim Dodd, the Everyday Astronaut here! After obsessing over SpaceX\u0027s BFS reentry system, I have been playing around with using airbrakes for dynamic drag control through reentry and landing. It works great, but it would be so much better if I could attach something to the stock airbrakes and have them move WITH the airbrakes...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI figured out how to attach to the airbrakes, but I can\u0027t get objects to move with them. I\u0027ve looked everywhere and cannot figure it out! Any help would be so greatly appreciated!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Damon","CreatedById":162728,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-06T15:31:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey! Welcome to the forums! (love your channel btw \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI would suggest you take a look at Animated Attachments. You can set things up so you can attach parts to animated or surface attachments.\u003Cbr\u003E\nCould be pretty useful to get that on airbrakes!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7244898038\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/175881-145-animatedattachment-211-now-with-animated-surface-attachments-2018-08-19/\u0026amp;\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe I should take a look at the airbrake system myself to see if I can make my BFS actuated fins move like that.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/PkgSksy.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:200px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 alt=\u0022PkgSksy.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/NlKRhPG.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:200px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 alt=\u0022NlKRhPG.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/PFtfFJu.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:200px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 alt=\u0022PFtfFJu.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"everydayastronaut","CreatedById":186030,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-06T15:37:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome!!!! Thank you!!! This might be exactly what I was looking for!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"everydayastronaut","CreatedById":186030,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-06T15:54:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWoah, I just noticed your amazing BFR/BFS model! When will that be available?!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceMouse","CreatedById":126931,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-06T18:12:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223463203\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221538837499\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022186030\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022everydayastronaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, everydayastronaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey everyone! Tim Dodd, the Everyday Astronaut here!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi Tim! Also a fan of your channel! Apologies though, not too familiar with air brake programming. Welcome to the forum!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bottle Rocketeer 500","CreatedById":178766,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-06T22:04:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/186030-everydayastronaut/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022186030\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/186030-everydayastronaut/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@everydayastronaut\u003C/a\u003E Here:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/166915-143-tundra-exploration-v114-august-16th-stockalike-spacex-falcon-9-dragon-v2-and-bfr/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/166915-143-tundra-exploration-v114-august-16th-stockalike-spacex-falcon-9-dragon-v2-and-bfr/\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223463320\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166915\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221538851650\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162728\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022damonvv\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, damonvv said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve added the 2018 BFR parts to Github!\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBE AWARE!\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EThis is pure a test build. \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDO NOT\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E use this with your current save!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EThings that are added:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nBFS Command pod\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBFS fuel tank\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBFS Engine Shroud\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSL Raptor engine\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n2 actuated fins\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n1 fixed tail fin\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBFB Interstage\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBFB Fuel tank\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBFB Engine cluster\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nMassive thank you to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JadeOfMaar\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for helping me out getting things fairly good balanced!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EAbout re-entry:\u003C/u\u003E Please be aware that the BFS is very unstable during re-entry. Any help or tips to improve this is highly appreciated!\u003Cbr\u003E\nThere\u0027s a craft file in the Ships/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E folder to try out and see how things are set up.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nHappy (test) launches!\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/NlKRhPG.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022NlKRhPG.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/NlKRhPG.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, welcome to the forums\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Damon","CreatedById":162728,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-07T11:40:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223463229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221538841296\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022186030\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022everydayastronaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, everydayastronaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWoah, I just noticed your amazing BFR/BFS model! When will that be available?!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey are available now for testing on my \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/damonvv/TundraExploration\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Egithub \u003C/a\u003E(be sure to have all the recommended mods listen in the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/166915-143-tundra-exploration-v114-august-16th-stockalike-spacex-falcon-9-dragon-v2-and-bfr/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nOnly problem I have so far is that the actuated fins don\u0027t actually work yet. I hope I can get this fixed at some point by using the airbrakes but that will take a while to get that balanced right I\u0027m afraid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-07T17:09:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/186030-everydayastronaut/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022186030\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/186030-everydayastronaut/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@everydayastronaut\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I\u0027m a big fan of your channel! Welcome to the forums!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would recommend checking out the rest of Tundra Exploration by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162728-damonvv/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162728\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162728-damonvv/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@damonvv\u003C/a\u003E. There are some great SpaceX parts!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fourfa","CreatedById":151713,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-07T21:06:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223463216\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221538839893\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162728\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022damonvv\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/6/2018 at 8:31 AM, damonvv said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey! Welcome to the forums! (love your channel btw \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI would suggest you take a look at Animated Attachments. You can set things up so you can attach parts to animated or surface attachments.\u003Cbr\u003E\nCould be pretty useful to get that on airbrakes!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1184719541\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/175881-145-animatedattachment-211-now-with-animated-surface-attachments-2018-08-19/\u0026amp;\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe I should take a look at the airbrake system myself to see if I can make my BFS actuated fins move like that.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/PkgSksy.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022PkgSksy.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/PkgSksy.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:200px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/NlKRhPG.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022NlKRhPG.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/NlKRhPG.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:200px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/PFtfFJu.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022PFtfFJu.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/PFtfFJu.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:200px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod has a lot of promise for adding layers of complexity with stock parts.\u00A0 I\u0027ve been playing with it a lot.\u00A0 I posted some in the thread a while back, but as-is you might need to write an additional cfg to change the attachment rules of some of the stock parts.\u00A0 IIRC the airbrakes don\u0027t allow you to attach to them, but they can if you change some values in their attach rules.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}